overview: The user initiated a request for a comprehensive aesthetic improvement
  of their sleep questionnaire application, which they felt was visually
  lacking. The agent began by thoroughly reviewing the existing styling across
  various components and sections. A new, calming sleep-themed color palette was
  introduced, replacing the generic blue/gray scheme. The main questionnaire
  form layout was significantly enhanced with decorative background elements, a
  redesigned progress indicator, and a subtle star pattern on card headers. The
  welcome screen was transformed with a hero section and feature cards, and all
  14 form sections were updated to use consistent, refined styling, moving away
  from plain gray boxes to more visually appealing card-like groupings. During
  the review, a console error related to null values being passed to input
  fields was identified. The agent implemented a fix in the Input component to
  convert null values to empty strings, resolving the error while preserving
  functionality for uncontrolled inputs. The overall outcome was a visually
  cohesive, professional, and calming application experience.
